Package com.google.monitoring.v3

Interface SnoozeServiceGrpc.AsyncService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SnoozeServiceGrpc.SnoozeServiceImplBase
    Enclosing class:
    SnoozeServiceGrpc
    public static interface SnoozeServiceGrpc.AsyncService
     The SnoozeService API is used to temporarily prevent an alert policy from
 generating alerts. A Snooze is a description of the criteria under which one
 or more alert policies should not fire alerts for the specified duration.

        default void createSnooze​(CreateSnoozeRequest request,
                          io.grpc.stub.StreamObserver<Snooze> responseObserver)

 criteria, from being opened. The `Snooze` applies for a specific time
 interval.
